Miss Hoadley Is Wed To Stephen B. Burke
Published: July 24, 1983









                    Gretchen Hoadley, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. David N. Hoadley of Brookside, N.J., was married yesterday to Stephen B. Burke, son of Mr. and Mrs. Daniel B. Burke of Rye, N.Y. The Rev. John Weber performed the ceremony at the Hilltop Presbyterian Church in Mendham, N.J.        

                    The couple graduated magna cum laude from Colgate University, where they were elected to Phi Beta Kappa. Mrs. Burke is a junior lending officer with the Manufacturers Hanover Trust Company in New York.  Her husband, who received an M.B.A. degree from Harvard, is an associate product manager with the breakfast foods division of the General Foods Corporation in White Plains.        

                    The bride's father is vice president of Smooth-On Inc., a plastics company in Gillette, N.J. The bridegroom's father is president of Capital Cities Communications in New York.        








 














 













 













 

